},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"identify where you struggle"}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"say thank you"}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"}],"tagName":"ol","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"I am doing this so they develop habits that will benefit them later in their\nwork life:"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"note progress"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":": it's important to capture the things you "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"did"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":". This is data\nwhich is very useful to keep stakeholders up to date. But it also provides a\ngreat source for review and appraisal meetings with managers. If they are not\nfrequent you will most likely have forgotten what you did a few months ago. A\nlog of things you did will help you identify important milestones you\nreached."}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"get clarity on goals"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":": working on software projects is highly complex and\nit's easy to loose sight of the bigger picture. Many small problems pile up\nand can easily obscure the initial goal that was set at the beginning of a\nproject. Stating (and reinforcing) the goals you work towards is important to\nkeep everyone aligned to work towards the same outcome. Clarity on thy "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Why?"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\nis neccessary to be able to quickly make daily decisions without depending on\nlong feedback cycles."}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"identify where you struggle"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":": I've put this in to normalize the fact that\nhitting blockers is normal, it is part of doing something new that hasn't\nbeen done before but also part of learning something new. Very few concepts\nwill just reveal themselves on the first look, it takes time and practice to\nunderstand them. Sharing what you struggle with also provides the opportunity\nfor team members to offer help and support; after all they might have had the\nsame issue in the past and know how to handle it. It is also important to\nenable the entire team to identify blockers that limit progress and evaluate\nwether to invest into resolving them immediately."}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"say thank you"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":": Actionable feedback is the most important input for a team\nto improve and grow. I especially highlight that it's about providing\nfeedback on what a person "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"did"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":", this offers them concrete feedback on their\nbehaviour and what is perceived as valuable by their team members. This can\nalso help them uncover skills they didn't know they posessed or didn't think\nof being valuable."}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"}],"tagName":"ol","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"https://twitter.com/marcobahn/status/1337353217592745995?embed"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://twitter.com/marcobahn/status/1337353217592745995?embed","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Below is the full README."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"properties":{"src":"//images.ctfassets.net/bncv3c2gt878/6YIY1eq7F4rNiztWfUO1hh/f55e6b19e0c49bf3db91be46ab9d31c4/50418980663_818d74ab0e_o_d.jpg?w=2268&h=4032","alt":"Waypoint finder at Gr√•kallen in Bymarka, Trondheim, Norway"},"children":[],"tagName":"img","type":"element"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#readme-office-hours","ariaLabel":"readme office hours permalink","className":["anchor","before"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"